  "text": "This study was designed to answer the question whether the tumor suppressor SIRT3 protein influences ROS production and HIF-1α activity in H. pyloriinfected gastric cancer cells. Using the established SIRT3 knockdown or SIRT3 overexpressing gastric epithelial cells to investigate the role of SIRT3, we confirmed results from previous studies that suggested that SIRT3 functions as a tumor suppressor due to the suppression of ROSmediated HIF-1α activation [CITATION_1] .",
